  "doc_id": "30019",
  "text": "It is shown in [CITATION_1] that for each labeling structure L with a total order on labels and each L-MLS ordering α of a graph G, α(1) is an OCF-vertex of G, i.e. satisfies the property: for each pair {y, z} of non-adjacent vertices in N (α(1)), there is a connected component C of G(V \\ N [α(1)]) such that y, z ∈ N G (C). However, the definition of a labeling structure given in [CITATION_2] is less general than the definition given in this paper, as condition IC is replaced by conditions (p1): l ≺ Inc(l, i) and (p2): if l ≺ l ′ then Inc(l, i)l ≺ Inc(l ′ , i): ((p1) and (p2) implies IC and IC implies (p1), but does not imply (p2). It turns out that the property of α(1) being an OCF-vertex does not extend to a labeling structure defined with condition IC instead of (p1) and (p2) (a counterexample can be built with some effort). It is the only result from [CITATION_3] that does not extend to a labeling structure defined with condition IC.",
